Utterances.UttText: Cage is a 46y/o M with a history of HTN, presenting with a 4 day history of exertional chest pain.

Phrases.PhraseText: a 46y/o M with a history of HTN,
presenting with a 4 day history of exertional chest pain.

Utterances.UttText: He notes that the onset occurred when he was carrying heavy groceries and felt a sudden, severe, heavy, deep aching pain.

Phrases.PhraseText: a sudden, severe, heavy, deep aching pain.

Utterances.UttText: The pain lasted between 5 to 10 minutes and was relieved by sitting in the car without moving.
He says that the pain did not radiate and was localized to the center of the sternum.

Phrases.PhraseText: localized to the center of the sternum.

Utterances.UttText: He states that he has experienced much milder pain at times of the past 4 months in the same location, always during exertion, these instances lasting 1-2 seconds.

Phrases.PhraseText: much milder pain at times of the past 4 months

Utterances.UttText: Also notes that he has symptoms of indigestion that only occur if he eats a very large meal, most often after lunch.

Less likely GERD related pain given exertional component.
